Property Documentation

◆ RefId

String^ IonicSecurity::SDK::GetResourcesRequest::Resource::RefId
getset

The reference ID.

Parameters
[in]msRefIdThe reference ID

The reference ID is an arbitrary string provided by callers in order to track created resources between the request and response. The order of the resources returned in the response is not guaranteed to be the same as the order of the request. When fetching multiple resources the reference ID is required in order to associate the resources returned in the response with the resources requested.

For example, if the request object specifies three resources, then the response object may contain those resources in any order. The correlation of resource request to resource response is determined by the reference ID.
